@node "History" "The History of TransFont's Creation"

 Some history...
@{lindent 1}
 v1.0  -  26.10.98

- First public version.

 v1.1  -  02.11.98

- @{lindent 3}Corrected a mistake bringing the program to an end, giving an incorrect explanation of the reason when the option Font Search in MCP was turned on.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Complete rewrote the procedure for processing Cycle Gadget. I hope now it'll work will all Cycle2Menu-like patches.@{lindent 1}

 v1.2  -  20.11.98  (intermediary version)

- Added the capability of writing a font without changes.

- @{lindent 3}Corrected a mistake in recoding several fonts from 866 and Koi8 codings.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added a DM2 recoding table. The difference between this coding and DM should really be just two bytes (code characters "A" and "a").@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added the capability to recode all font sizes in one pass.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added the capability of changing @{" Font ID " LINK "Font_ID"} of the font being converted, suitable for storinga little information (up to 31 characters), for example, the date of font creation, coding, version number, etc.@{lindent 1}

 v2.0  -  7.01.99

- @{lindent 3}The biggest changes affected the GUI interface, due to which there was a delay in the program's output. There's no reason to describe all the new things here since it affects only a very limited area (in my view).:@{lindent 3}

Maximum number of fonts in font name ListView - 1000
Maximum number of fonts in font size ListView - 100
@{lindent 1}
- @{lindent 3}Added the capability of exporting a font in the source file, for now only for one font size and only in asm format; if anyone needs it in C - write me.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added a new parameter CLI/ToolType: VIEWSTRING=V/K.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Corrected a mistake of the first 4 bytes of the font header, as a result of which some programs (for example DOpus5) could not correctly identify the fonts being converted by TransFont.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Corrected the "hard sign" (tverdiy znak) character in the KOI-8 coding (from $A2 to $FF), according to new intelligence data. ;)@{lindent 1}

 v2.1  -  7.02.99

- Localization done.

- @{lindent 3}Two parameters added CLI/ToolType: FONTNAME=FN/K, FONTSIZE=FS/N.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Corrected a conflict with DOpus5 when programm's AppIcon movied to the Tools menu.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added a complete (including the lower half of the ASCII table) recoding when used external table.@{lindent 1}

 v2.2  -  28.03.99

- @{lindent 3}Fixed a sadly bug of previous version, as a result of which all internal table convertings didn't work properly...  Sorry.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Added English guide.  Thanks to ATO!@{lindent 1}

 v2.3  -  12.05.99

- @{lindent 3}Added ColorFont support.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Bugfix.  Enforcer hit while accessing to not existing device.@{lindent 1}

 v2.3a -  19.05.99

- @{lindent 3}"BLine" parameter was changed to "Colors" - number of colors.@{lindent 1}

- @{lindent 3}Some bugfix.@{lindent 1}

@endnode
